Title: Black Holes in Two Dimensional Dilaton Gravity and Nonlinear

Klein-Gordon SolitonAuthors: Hyeon-Min Johng, Hak-Soo Shin (E-Mail

Comments: 9 pages, no figures, latex

Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A10 (1995) 4681-4688

Two-dimensional dilaton gravity coupled to a Klein-Gordon matter field with aquartic interaction term is considered. The theory has a classical solutionwhich exhibits black hole formation by a soliton. The geometry of black holeinduced by a soliton is investigated.